OL,3,CSub-postmaster only realised extent of
OL,4,Cscandal when he saw ITV drama
OL,6,FThe Tizzards were never convicted of a
OL,7,Fcrime but had paid thousands of pounds
OL,8,Fof their own money into the system to
OL,9,Fmake up the shortfall.
OL,11,FThey are due to get #75,000 in
OL,12,Fcompensation but say altogether the
OL,13,Fscandal has cost them far more.
OL,15,FMr Tizzard said "When I found out I
OL,16,Fwatched 'Mr Bates vs the Post Office'.
OL,17,FWe knew there were problems with
OL,18,FHorizon because it was in the press,
OL,19,Fbut the extent of it - we never
OL,20,Frealised until we saw the programme."
